9. Click **Commit changes** (green button)
10. Click **Commit changes** again in the popup

#### Step 1.3: Get the Raw File URL

11. Click on your `dashboard.json` file
12. Click **Raw** button (top right of file content)
13. **Copy the URL** from your browser - it should look like:
```
https://raw.githubusercontent.com/YOUR-USERNAME/podcast-dashboard-data/main/dashboard.json
```

14. **Save this URL** - you'll need it for Logic Apps!

---

### **PART 2: Update Logic App (20 min)**

#### Step 2.1: Open Logic App Designer

1. Go to **Azure Portal** â†’ Your Logic App
2. Click **Logic app designer**

#### Step 2.2: Add HTTP Action (Get Data from GitHub)

3. Click **+ New step** (after your Recurrence trigger)
4. Search: `HTTP`
5. Select **HTTP**

#### Configure HTTP Action:

6. **Method**: `GET`
7. **URI**: Paste your raw GitHub URL from Step 1.3
```
   https://raw.githubusercontent.com/YOUR-USERNAME/podcast-dashboard-data/main/dashboard.json
